Exaggerate: The claim exaggerates the number of instances of voter fraud in Wood County, Ohio by stating that there were multiple instances when there is no evidence to support this.
Contradict fact: The claim contradicts the fact that neither presidential candidate received 100 percent of the votes in any of the county's precincts.
Lack enough support: The claim lacks enough support as there is no evidence provided to back up the allegations of voter fraud.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that the removal of GOP inspectors from polling locations resulted in voter fraud, without providing any evidence to support this assumption.
Exist alternative explanation: The claim fails to consider alternative explanations for the discrepancies in voter registrations, such as the large population of college students who register to vote in Wood County but later move away.
